SIMPLE: fettling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fettling
<hw>Fet"tling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>A mixture of ore, cinders, etc., used to line
the hearth of a puddling furnace.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> <note>[It is
commonly called <altname>fix</altname> in the United States.]</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Pottery)</fld> <def>The operation of shaving or
smoothing the surface of undried clay ware.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fetuous</ent>⟦br⟧
